Category:Wikipedia semi-protected templates - Wikipedia,"This category contains templates which have been semi-protected. This is usually done in response to vandalism or other unconstructive editing, or when the template is widely used, meaning that such vandalism is very noticeable – so-called ""high-risk"" templates. Semi-protection prevents a page being edited by anonymous or newly registered users; more vulnerable templates may be fully protected, which prevents them being edited except by administrators.
To add a template to this category, use {{Pp-template}}. This should only be done if the template is in fact semi-protected – adding the template does not in itself protect the page.
"
Category:Wikipedia semi-protected templates - Wikipedia,"The following 200 pages are in this category, out of approximately 11,528 total. This list may not reflect recent changes (learn more).
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"This template is used to identify a film stub about a 1990s comedy. It uses {{asbox}}, which is a meta-template designed to ease the process of creating and maintaining stub templates.
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"Typing {{1990s-comedy-film-stub}} produces the message shown at the beginning, and adds the article to the following category:
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"This is a stub template. A brief explanation of these templates follows; for full details please consult Wikipedia:Stub. 
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"A stub is an article containing only a few sentences of text which is too short to provide encyclopedic coverage of a subject.
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"Further information can be found at:
"
Template:1990s-comedy-film-stub - Wikipedia,"New stub templates and categories (collectively ""stub types"") should not be created without prior proposal at Wikipedia:WikiProject Stub sorting/Proposals. This allows for the proper coordination of all stub types across Wikipedia, and for the checking of any new stub type for possible problems prior to its creation.
