Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Before a file can be used, it must be uploaded to either Wikipedia or the Wikimedia Commons sister project. Uploading to Commons is recommended as files can be used by other sister projects. Files being used under fair use provisions must be stored on Wikipedia. The markup is the same regardless of where it is uploaded.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"The following sound formats may be uploaded:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Normally, sound files are presented on Wikipedia pages using the Template:Listen or its related templates.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"This is an example, displaying common usage:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"This template links to an audio file for quick listening. It is meant to be used inline with text, for pronunciations and the like.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"{{Audio|name of sound file|text to use as link to soundfile}}
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Example:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"gives this:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Note that a printout of the page will remove the ""help·info"" bit and give:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Setting |help=no disables the ""help/info"" links. If this is done the template {{inline audio}} must be shown on the page.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Normally, sound files are presented on Wikipedia pages using the Template:Listen or its related templates. However, it is also possible to present an audio file without any template.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"[[File:Accordion chords-01.ogg]]
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"The parameter |thumbmay be used to give the file a caption. That will also float the playbutton to the right.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"[[File:Accordion chords-01.ogg|thumb|Caption]]
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"The size of the player can be specified:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"[[File:Accordion chords-01.ogg|233px]]
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Note that the seek bar becomes visible for sizes of 233px and above.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"Combining size and caption:
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"[[File:Accordion chords-01.ogg|thumb|240px|Caption]]
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"None of these examples provide links to Wikipedia:Media help. Thus, whenever this method is used, the Template:Inline audio must be shown on the page.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"To link to a description page, put a colon before the prefix.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"You can also link directly to the file using ""Media:"" instead of ""File:"". This method must not be used solely for a file under a license which requires attribution, such as CC-BY licenses.
"
Help:Sound file markup - Wikipedia,"In both cases piped links also work.
