"
Help:HTML in wikitext - Wikipedia,"<input> is used to create forms. The <inputbox> extension tag is used to create a text box with a button.
"
Help:HTML in wikitext - Wikipedia,"HTML Tidy is an outdated HTML4 library that is slated for removal. Tidy parses the MediaWiki output and cleans it up to increase the likelihood that valid HTML4 is rendered. For example, with Tidy enabled, <br>, </br>, <br/>, <br.> all rendered as <br />. Tidy is not enabled for MediaWiki interface pages. Tidy was never perfect and has been known to introduce errors.
"
Help:HTML in wikitext - Wikipedia,"In some pages in the MediaWiki namespace, typically the short messages like button labels, HTML is not parsed, and tags will be exposed.
"
Help:HTML in wikitext - Wikipedia,"User and sitewide CSS and JavaScript pages are interpreted as if inside a <pre> block. See Help:User style.
"
Help:HTML in wikitext - Wikipedia,"The MediaWiki software attempts to fix HTML errors, but it does not catch all of them. Where HTML is used, it is helpful to verify it with the W3C Markup Validation Service.
"
