"
Wikipedia:Shortcut - Wikipedia,"The second of these is no longer in use at all.
"
Wikipedia:Shortcut - Wikipedia,"Portals have occasionally also used spaces in shortcuts, e.g. ""Portal X"", or ""X portal"".  Most mainspace pages containing the word are articles or redirects to articles.
"
Wikipedia:Shortcut - Wikipedia,"Technical note: The links in the table go to a page where the term prefix is not used in the meaning as it has in this section.  Rather, the code PrefixIndex there means, as it does for the search parameter, ""the beginning string of characters in a title"", whether that string ends before, during or after the colon character in a page name.
"
